        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 3:54PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 354 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles east of High Rock Lake, or 10 miles north of Badin Lake, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
High Point, Randleman, Thomasville, Archdale, Trinity, Denton,
Gordontown, Randleman Regional Reservior Marina, Newsom, and High
Rock Boat Dock Marina.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
